      "Crane was taken out of service",
      "Apache Corporation retraining crane operator"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 2, 2023, at 12:30 hours, a crane boom contacted the boom stop at High Island A 382 F facility during crane operations. The boom was raised to too high an angle, causing the load block to swing into the crane boom and damage the heel section cords. The estimated replacement cost was $50,000. No injuries or pollution were reported. The incident was attributed to crane operator inattentiveness regarding boom angle and failure of the high angle kick out safety system.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Retraining of crane operator"
    ],
